@startuml 04-seq-dragdrop
' docs/uml/04-seq-dragdrop.puml
' Sequence diagram: Kanban drag-and-drop with optimistic updates and WebSocket sync.
' Что показывает: полный флоу перетаскивания задачи с оптимистичным обновлением, WS broadcast и откатом при ошибке.
' Кому полезна: frontend- и backend-разработчикам для понимания real-time синхронизации.

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam maxMessageSize 200
skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor #333
    LifeLineBorderColor #666
    ParticipantBorderColor #333
    ParticipantBackgroundColor #E8EAF6
    ParticipantFontSize 13
    NoteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
}

actor "User A\n(dragging)" as UserA #E3F2FD
actor "User B\n(viewing)" as UserB #F3E5F5
participant "NestJS API" as API #E8F5E9
database "PostgreSQL" as DB #FFF3E0
participant "Socket.IO\nGateway" as WS #FFEBEE

== Drag & Drop Flow ==

UserA -> UserA : onDragEnd:\ncalculate newOrder = midpoint(prev, next)\nnewStatus = target column status

UserA -> UserA : React Query:\noptimistic update (instant)
note right of UserA #C8E6C9
    UI updates immediately.
    Card moves to new column.
    No network delay visible.
end note

UserA -> API : PATCH /issues/{id}/order\n{ newOrder, newStatus, columnId }
activate API

API -> DB : UPDATE issues\nSET "order" = $newOrder,\n    status = $newStatus\nWHERE id = $issueId
DB --> API : OK (1 row)

API -> DB : INSERT INTO issue_changelog\n{ field: 'status', old_value, new_value }
DB --> API : OK

API -> API : Check: |newOrder - neighborOrder| < 0.001?

alt order gap too small → REBALANCE
    API -> DB : SELECT id, "order" FROM issues\nWHERE project_id = $pid AND status = $status\nORDER BY "order" ASC
    DB --> API : all issues in column
    API -> DB : BEGIN TRANSACTION
    API -> DB : UPDATE issues SET "order" = 1.0 WHERE id = 'a'\nUPDATE issues SET "order" = 2.0 WHERE id = 'b'\n... (reassign integer orders)
    API -> DB : COMMIT
    DB --> API : OK
end

alt success
    API -> WS : EventEmitter.emit('issue.moved',\n{ issueId, newStatus, newOrder, movedBy, projectId })
    activate WS
    WS -> WS : find rooms matching\nproject:{projectId}:tenant:*
    WS -> UserB : emit 'issue:moved'\n{ issueId, newStatus, newOrder, movedBy }
    deactivate WS

    UserB -> UserB : queryClient.setQueryData:\napply move in board cache
    note right of UserB #E3F2FD
        User B sees the card
        move in real-time.
    end note

    API --> UserA : 200 OK { ...updatedIssue }
    UserA -> UserA : React Query: confirm\n(cache already matches)

else error (DB conflict / constraint violation)
    API --> UserA : 409 Conflict\n{ message: "Order conflict" }
    UserA -> UserA : useMoveIssue.onError:\nqueryClient.invalidateQueries(['board', projectId])
    note right of UserA #FFCDD2
        Optimistic update rolled back.
        Board refetched from server.
    end note
    UserA -> API : GET /projects/{id}/board
    API -> DB : SELECT columns + issues
    DB --> API : fresh board data
    API --> UserA : 200 { columns: [...] }
end

deactivate API

@enduml
